<div type="definition">
<p>PLACE in SPACE CONTAINING the SUN, the MOON and the STARS.</p>
    <div type="definition" resp="#CH" modified="2021-04-07T03:25:00.379+09:00">
            <p>PLACE CONTAINING the SUN, the MOON and the STARS.</p>
        </div>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. The current word for the sky, and for Heaven, is tiān 天 (ant. dì 地 "earth").</p>
<p>2. Qián 乾 (ant. kūn 坤 "metaphysical: Earth") is a learned "metaphyisical" way of referring to Heaven.</p>
<p>3. Cāng 蒼 is a poetic word for blue sky, but the word is not apparently attested in pre-Buddhist texts.</p>
        </div>
